CNCP v1 22760
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#8117: style v-bind should have prepend \"url(\" and append \")\" when the variable is an url/asset/module",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:39.371810+00:00",
  "text": "style v-bind should have prepend \"url(\" and append \")\" when the variable is an url/asset/module\n\n### What problem does this feature solve?\n\nstyle v-bind should have prepend \"url(\" and append \")\" when the variable is an url/asset/module\n\n### What does the proposed API look like?\n\n```\r\n<script lang=\"ts\" setup>\r\nimport shape from \"@/assets/shape.svg\";\r\n</script>\r\n<style scoped lang=scss>\r\ndiv {\r\n    background-image: v-bind(shape);\r\n}\r\n</style>\r\n```\r\n\r\nsince `background-image: v-bind(shape);` converts to `var(--3d872d92-shape)` and wrapping it with url is not allowed.\r\nthe v-bind should set this scss variable `--3d872d92-shape: url(/src/assets/shape.svg)` instead of `--3d872d92-shape: /src/assets/shape.svg`.",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request"
  ],
  "embedding": {
    "model": "granite-embedding-278m-multilingual",
    "dim": 768,
